		<h3>POODLE: Padding Oracle On Downgraded Legacy Encryption</h3>
		<h4>March 26th, 2015</h4>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Google's security team has discovered a fundamental flaw in OpenSSL 3.0, allowing malicious users to break the encryption and view private data. This flaw is so fundamental to the protocol that the solution to this issue is to not allow use of OpenSSL 3.0. You find more information regarding this vulnerability in OpenSSL 3.0 on <a href="https://www.openssl.org/~bodo/ssl-poodle.pdf">OpenSSL's website</a>.</p>
