		<h3>YOICS Account Takeover Vulnerability</h3>
		<h4>February 4th, 2015</h4>
		<div class="content">
			<p>YOICS, a secure cloud networking system used by CISCO, Astak, and Philips have discovered a vulnerability with their user authentication system, resulting in malicious users being able to take over other users' accounts. This vulnerability was reported and fixed in 3 days. You can find more information regarding how this vulnerability could of been exploited on <a href="http://www.ifc0nfig.com/yoics-account-takeover-vulnerability/">Paul Price's blog</a>.</p>
